string.name: child_component_response
string.value: Child component:Clicking will respond to bubble events

string.name: child_component_no_response
string.value: Child component:Clicking will not respond to bubble events

string.name: parent_component_text
string.value: The gray area is the parent component area, and clicking can trigger the parent component event

string.name: click_event_alert_dialog_message
string.value: Sub component click event triggers dialog window

string.name: click_event_title
string.value: Function Description: When the enabled attribute value of a subcomponent is false, turn off the enable switch, click on the subcomponent event bubble (subcomponent passes an onClick event to the parent component), turn on the enable switch, and click on the subcomponent event bubble to be blocked. (enabled: controls whether components can interact and respond to click events, touch events, drag events, button events, focus events, and mouse events in an interactive state.)

string.name: touch_event_title
string.value: Function Description: When the enabled attribute value of a subcomponent is true, turn off the enable switch, click on the subcomponent event bubble (subcomponent passes onTouch events to the parent component), turn on the enable switch, and click on the subcomponent event bubble to be blocked.
